<DOC><DOCNO> DOE1-36-0605 </DOCNO><TEXT>In this paper are discussed the recent contributions of Molecular Dynamicsand Vibrational Spectroscopy (Infrared and Raman) to the understandingof the structural and molecular properties which underline the processof electrical conduction in conjugated polymers. It is shown that spectroscopy,at present, provides one way of aiming at detail molecular features witha resolving power of a few Angstroms even on complicated systems. Themechanism of doping can be studied in detail. 41 refs.</TEXT></DOC>